So, why not skip Kishi
and take care of Keita Iwazaki next?

133
00:08:22.735 --> 00:08:23.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's not going to work.

134
00:08:24.770 --> 00:08:26.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've decided
we're going in order this time.

135
00:08:27.573 --> 00:08:30.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have to follow the rules,
just like in a game.

136
00:08:30.810 --> 00:08:33.713  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But if we have no idea where he is,
then we're stuck.

137
00:08:35.114 --> 00:08:37.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, all games have their cheats, right?

138
00:08:38.251 --> 00:08:40.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If we don't know where Kishi is,

139
00:08:40.786 --> 00:08:43.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we find out where the men
assigned to protect him are.

140
00:08:44.690 --> 00:08:47.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, just hack
the Metropolitan Police Department.

141
00:08:48.194 --> 00:08:49.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Isn't that impossible?

142
00:08:49.629 --> 00:08:52.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No,
that's one of the things that can be done.

143
00:08:52.798 --> 00:08:55.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Naturally, it'll take a few days
since we're starting from scratch,

144
00:08:55.935 --> 00:08:57.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but just like with the Ministry,

145
00:08:58.037 --> 00:09:01.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Metro P.D. server
should have a back door.

146
00:09:01.173 --> 00:09:04.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, all I have to do is borrow that.
So, if I can just find it...

147
00:09:04.243 --> 00:09:05.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's he talking about?

148
00:09:05.611 --> 00:09:08.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[hacker] I'll sneak in that back door,
and close it behind me when I leave...

149
00:09:08.848 --> 00:09:11.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] Basically... he's using a cheat.

150
00:09:14.153 --> 00:09:17.323  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
YUJI KISHI

151
00:09:18.925 --> 00:09:19.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[hacker] It's done.

152
00:09:21.594 --> 00:09:23.029  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Security assigned for Yuji Kishi.

153
00:09:23.629 --> 00:09:25.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There are two units of riot police,

154
00:09:25.197 --> 00:09:28.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as well as people drummed up from Traffic
and Community Safety Divisions.

155
00:09:28.868 --> 00:09:32.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I guess they can't afford to be too picky
when it comes to choosing personnel.

156
00:09:33.606 --> 00:09:34.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where are they?

157
00:09:37.176 --> 00:09:38.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In the mountains.

158
00:09:42.315 --> 00:09:43.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighing]

159
00:09:48.087 --> 00:09:50.089  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why don't you try to settle down a bit?

160
00:09:50.756 --> 00:09:52.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This isn't doing any good.

161
00:09:54.293 --> 00:09:55.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, you're right.

162
00:10:01.801 --> 00:10:03.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[thump on door]

163
00:10:03.603 --> 00:10:04.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who's there?!

164
00:10:06.606 --> 00:10:09.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasping]

165
00:10:10.876 --> 00:10:11.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A ghost.

166
00:10:11.811 --> 00:10:12.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[thud]
-[Kishi groaning]

167
00:10:22.254 --> 00:10:23.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all gasping]

168
00:10:32.999 --> 00:10:36.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Ogura] 
There are two ways to get rid of an IBM.

169
00:10:37.303 --> 00:10:42.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Wait for it to disappear,
or have another IBM hit it in the head.

170
00:10:48.748 --> 00:10:50.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If two IBMs collide with each other,

171
00:10:51.017 --> 00:10:54.353  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
particles bearing different information
get mixed together.

172
00:10:55.254 --> 00:10:57.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Basically, their wires get crossed.

173
00:10:58.758 --> 00:11:02.161  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Communication between particles
that should be re-bonding is suspended,

174
00:11:02.662 --> 00:11:05.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and as a result, they are neutralized.

175
00:11:06.065 --> 00:11:06.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[phone ringing]

176
00:11:08.234 --> 00:11:10.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Turn off your phone during class,
four-eyes.

177
00:11:10.970 --> 00:11:11.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is Tosaki.

178
00:11:13.439 --> 00:11:14.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that?

179
00:11:15.274 --> 00:11:16.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How did they find out?

180
00:11:17.410 --> 00:11:18.844  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[inhales sharply]

181
00:11:18.911 --> 00:11:23.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, I leave that to you.
I'll head back immediately.

182
00:11:25.117 --> 00:11:26.085  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is it Dr. Kishi?

183
00:11:26.886 --> 00:11:28.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, they got him.

184
00:11:29.855 --> 00:11:33.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just when they'd increased security,
he was assassinated by an IBM. Damn it.

185
00:11:34.427 --> 00:11:36.128  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How did they find out where he was?

186
00:11:36.395 --> 00:11:37.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We don't know.

187
00:11:38.364 --> 00:11:42.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we don't know how they found out,
it doesn't matter where the targets hide.

188
00:11:43.069 --> 00:11:44.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can't stall for time.

189
00:11:44.904 --> 00:11:47.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And that means
that we've lost one of our advantages.

190
00:11:51.243 --> 00:11:52.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you...

191
00:11:53.079 --> 00:11:56.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I hear you've been slacking
on your IBM training lately.

192
00:11:57.883 --> 00:12:01.153  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Our greatest strength is your IBM.

193
00:12:02.021 --> 00:12:05.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You need to master using it as soon
as possible. Have I made myself clear?

194
00:12:13.332 --> 00:12:17.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I guess it looks like
you are this team's telomere.

195
00:12:20.172 --> 00:12:21.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
WARNING: MOUNTAIN FIRES
NO FIRES ALLOWED

196
00:12:21.207 --> 00:12:23.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[silenced gunshots]

197
00:12:24.009 --> 00:12:25.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] The enemy will be armed.

198
00:12:25.478 --> 00:12:28.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
At the very least, you should learn
how to use weapons like these.

199
00:12:31.750 --> 00:12:34.353  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
First try holding it. Next...

200
00:12:44.530 --> 00:12:46.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I like how machines do as they're told.

201
00:12:48.767 --> 00:12:51.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Nakano]
Huh? There's no rapid-fire button?

202
00:12:51.070 --> 00:12:53.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Shut up!
Just listen to what I'm telling you.

203
00:13:00.212 --> 00:13:01.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nakano speaks in Japanese]

204
00:13:01.380 --> 00:13:02.381  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's not working, huh?

205
00:13:02.982 --> 00:13:03.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hand it over.

206
00:13:05.885 --> 00:13:06.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here.

207
00:13:07.086 --> 00:13:08.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

208
00:13:09.855 --> 00:13:10.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

209
00:13:11.857 --> 00:13:13.325  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[gunshot]
-[grunting]

210
00:13:13.392 --> 00:13:15.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You fool! Why did you let go?

211
00:13:16.462 --> 00:13:17.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My hand hurts.

212
00:13:18.264 --> 00:13:19.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you a girl?

213
00:13:19.865 --> 00:13:22.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hey, whatever.
It's not like I can help it if it hurts!

214
00:13:22.868 --> 00:13:23.536  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sucks teeth]

215
00:13:32.011 --> 00:13:33.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Excuse--
-[grunts]

216
00:13:35.447 --> 00:13:38.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Nagai. You need something?

217
00:13:41.086 --> 00:13:41.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

218
00:13:43.189 --> 00:13:44.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Never mind. It can wait.

219
00:13:56.335 --> 00:13:59.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Manabe was saying that
he thought you needed something.

220
00:14:01.207 --> 00:14:05.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I just thought it'd be useful to have data
like everyone's height and weight.

221
00:14:05.477 --> 00:14:07.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I can do just fine without it.

222
00:14:07.880 --> 00:14:08.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay, then.

223
00:14:10.516 --> 00:14:13.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you...? Are you lonely?

224
00:14:13.252 --> 00:14:14.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?!

225
00:14:14.887 --> 00:14:15.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I guess not.

226
00:14:17.289 --> 00:14:20.059  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then... maybe you're just lost.

227
00:14:24.997 --> 00:14:27.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're wondering if your
unsympathetic behavior is appropriate,

228
00:14:27.967 --> 00:14:33.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you're also wondering if maybe
you should... somehow try and change.

229
00:14:35.040 --> 00:14:36.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is that right?
-No!

230
00:14:38.310 --> 00:14:41.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Look, I haven't said a single thing
that doesn't make sense.

231
00:14:42.081 --> 00:14:44.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm making entirely logical decisions.

232
00:14:44.550 --> 00:14:46.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What is it that you think
I need to change?

233
00:14:48.220 --> 00:14:50.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes... you're exactly right.

234
00:14:51.657 --> 00:14:52.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

235
00:14:53.993 --> 00:14:57.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That Nakano kid is good at gaining
other people's trust.

236
00:14:58.063 --> 00:15:00.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you were in the same class at school,

237
00:15:01.133 --> 00:15:03.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he'd be the popular kid
and you'd just be some loser.

238
00:15:04.470 --> 00:15:06.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But this isn't school.

239
00:15:07.506 --> 00:15:11.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're going to need to make decisions
that go beyond morals or emotions.

240
00:15:13.045 --> 00:15:17.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you're... You're able to do that.

241
00:15:21.153 --> 00:15:23.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nagai] I know all that.

242
00:15:23.956 --> 00:15:24.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] I see.

243
00:15:25.524 --> 00:15:27.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I must have misunderstood.

244
00:15:32.932 --> 00:15:34.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My father was an excellent surgeon.

245
00:15:36.669 --> 00:15:38.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He was close with his patients.

246
00:15:38.570 --> 00:15:41.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
After they recovered,
they'd send him letters every year.

247
00:15:41.941 --> 00:15:44.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But that was also his greatest weakness.

248
00:15:45.544 --> 00:15:48.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When I was 9, one of his patients
couldn't find a kidney donor,

249
00:15:48.580 --> 00:15:52.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and my father tried to help by getting
involved in black-market organ trading.

250
00:15:53.419 --> 00:15:55.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In the end, my father lost everything.

251
00:15:58.090 --> 00:15:59.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I won't make the same mistake.

252
00:16:00.459 --> 00:16:01.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not an idiot.

253
00:16:03.262 --> 00:16:05.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's no seniority
when it comes to intelligence.

254
00:16:06.598 --> 00:16:08.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do as you will.

255
00:16:09.034 --> 00:16:11.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Our job is to simply follow
whatever the plan asks of us.

256
00:16:19.745 --> 00:16:24.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have a list of the most important points
of our Sato countermeasure strategies.

257
00:16:25.017 --> 00:16:27.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I expect you all to memorize them.
-[all grunt]

258
00:16:27.653 --> 00:16:28.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Nakano.
-[Nakano] Huh?

259
00:16:29.021 --> 00:16:30.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You especially.

260
00:16:31.557 --> 00:16:32.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What does this say?

261
00:16:33.158 --> 00:16:35.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh? "Invasion."

262
00:16:35.427 --> 00:16:37.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh... Oh!

263
00:16:37.529 --> 00:16:38.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[chuckles]
-[Shimomura sighs]

264
00:16:38.764 --> 00:16:39.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Manabe] Hey.

265
00:16:40.332 --> 00:16:43.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You expect us to do this?
We're not Ajin, you know.

266
00:16:44.169 --> 00:16:46.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai, this was your idea, wasn't it?

267
00:16:47.306 --> 00:16:48.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, so?

268
00:16:49.408 --> 00:16:50.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

269
00:16:51.710 --> 00:16:53.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Looks like it'll be fun.

270
00:17:03.288 --> 00:17:05.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[urinating]
-[door opens]

271
00:17:05.391 --> 00:17:06.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nakano] Hey.

272
00:17:08.394 --> 00:17:09.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you want?

273
00:17:10.195 --> 00:17:11.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you...?

274
00:17:12.564 --> 00:17:15.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Well, do you know a good way to die?
-Huh?

275
00:17:15.300 --> 00:17:17.536  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
