is basically luck.

277
00:17:21.306 --> 00:17:22.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

278
00:17:22.241 --> 00:17:26.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
An Ajin's IBM particles
are at their densest when they regenerate.

279
00:17:26.111 --> 00:17:26.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

280
00:17:27.046 --> 00:17:30.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
However, unusual effects can occur
during that time.

281
00:17:30.382 --> 00:17:32.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You could call it a tunnel effect.

282
00:17:32.384 --> 00:17:34.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What tunnel do I need to go to?
-[grunts]

283
00:17:37.823 --> 00:17:40.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'll be going to the great beyond.

284
00:17:41.794 --> 00:17:45.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you want to force your IBM to manifest,
there's just one thing to do.

285
00:17:45.631 --> 00:17:48.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And that's dying over and over again.

286
00:17:48.267 --> 00:17:49.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah...

287
00:17:50.169 --> 00:17:51.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've already died an awful lot.

288
00:17:51.837 --> 00:17:54.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Might take a couple tries,
or a few hundred,

289
00:17:54.473 --> 00:17:56.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if you want to win that trip to Hawaii.

290
00:18:00.212 --> 00:18:01.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nakano groans]

291
00:18:03.148 --> 00:18:05.284  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
With this,
you can keep dying automatically.

292
00:18:05.551 --> 00:18:06.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Even sleep through it.

293
00:18:07.553 --> 00:18:08.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And there won't be any pain.

294
00:18:15.160 --> 00:18:15.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

295
00:18:16.628 --> 00:18:19.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay then. I'm ready.

296
00:18:19.364 --> 00:18:21.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's there to be afraid of?

297
00:18:21.200 --> 00:18:24.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[chuckles] Well, how do you
just let yourself die like that?

298
00:18:24.436 --> 00:18:25.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You do it, too, don't you?

299
00:18:26.305 --> 00:18:27.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I'm always scared.

300
00:18:28.340 --> 00:18:30.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean, you never know, right?

301
00:18:31.143 --> 00:18:32.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe the next time I won't come back.

302
00:18:34.613 --> 00:18:37.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's just a rumor,
but I've heard that an Ajin in China

303
00:18:38.417 --> 00:18:40.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
has set a record by dying 2,000 times.

304
00:18:41.253 --> 00:18:42.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And the count is still rising.

305
00:18:43.388 --> 00:18:45.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wow, they sure go all out.

306
00:18:45.290 --> 00:18:49.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Whatever it takes...
or else we'll never move forward.

307
00:18:50.562 --> 00:18:52.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's nothing to be afraid of.

308
00:18:53.365 --> 00:18:55.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're pretty amazing.

309
00:18:57.803 --> 00:18:59.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just hurry up and die.

310
00:19:02.474 --> 00:19:04.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nakano] Hey, are you leaving?

311
00:19:04.376 --> 00:19:07.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nagai] What, are you a child? I'm busy.

312
00:19:07.346 --> 00:19:09.381  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nakano] Oh, that's cold, man.

313
00:19:19.858 --> 00:19:22.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[inhales deeply, then exhales]

314
00:19:26.265 --> 00:19:29.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Nagai] <i>That's right. </i>
<i>There's nothing to be afraid of.</i>

315
00:19:49.254 --> 00:19:50.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do what you want!

316
00:19:57.396 --> 00:20:00.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not ordering you around anymore.
Do what you like.

317
00:20:05.337 --> 00:20:07.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know that.

318
00:20:08.273 --> 00:20:10.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not an idiot.

319
00:20:13.579 --> 00:20:16.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Man, I'm surrounded by idiots.

320
00:20:19.718 --> 00:20:20.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[snickers]

321
00:20:22.421 --> 00:20:23.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nagai grunts]

322
00:20:23.388 --> 00:20:26.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Serves you right.
-Why you...

323
00:20:27.459 --> 00:20:28.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[punches thumping]

324
00:20:29.561 --> 00:20:30.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[footsteps approaching]

325
00:20:45.277 --> 00:20:48.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-There are plenty of other seats--
-That friend of yours is in juvenile hall.

326
00:20:49.314 --> 00:20:49.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

327
00:20:50.682 --> 00:20:51.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That day...

328
00:20:53.352 --> 00:20:54.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The day you were sent to the lab.</i>

329
00:20:57.856 --> 00:20:59.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The police went ahead and arrested him.

330
00:21:03.595 --> 00:21:05.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why are you telling me this now?

331
00:21:11.403 --> 00:21:13.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you planning to use Kaito
to threaten me...

332
00:21:14.806 --> 00:21:16.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
just in case I were to betray you?

333
00:21:17.042 --> 00:21:19.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, do you mean the same way
you used my fiancée?

334
00:21:22.581 --> 00:21:24.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
